[indent]
[font_size=20][b]Sarah Okafor[/b][/font_size]
[color=#666660]Investigative Reporter — Financial Crime & Corporate Accountability[/color]

─────────────────────────────────────────────────

[color=#444440]Sarah covers financial crime, corporate malfeasance, and data privacy. She has been reporting for The Signal since 2021 and has broken several high-profile stories involving corporate fraud and regulatory failure.

Before joining The Signal, she spent six years at a national broadsheet and two years as a researcher for a parliamentary select committee on financial services oversight.

She is a fellow of the Reuters Institute for the Study of Journalism.[/color]

─────────────────────────────────────────────────

[b]Recent work[/b]

[color=#444440]· Data brokers and the quiet trade in your medical history
· The compliance consultancy that wasn't: how audit firms become cover stories
· Who owns your financial records? The answer is more complicated than you'd think[/color]

─────────────────────────────────────────────────

[b]Secure contact[/b]

[color=#444440]If you have information and you're not sure what to do with it — reach out. Everything is treated with the strictest confidence. I do not share sources. I do not store identifying metadata.

